<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Err" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Err,</orth> 1) to deviate from the true course, to stray: <cit><quote>if I can check my --ing love, I will,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 213</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my jealous aim might e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 28</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 62</bibl>. 100 (<emph>against all rules;</emph> cf. <emph>error</emph> in <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.165" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 165</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.227" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 227</bibl> <emph>(nature --ing from itself).</emph><lb />2) to be mistaken: <bibl n="shak. son 131.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 131, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.137.13" default="NO" valid="yes">137, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.317" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 317</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.4.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 4, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 43</bibl>.
<lb />3) to offend: <cit><quote>whether you had not sometime in your life --ed in this point,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 15</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 8, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 3, 22</bibl>.
<lb />4) to wander, to roam: <cit><quote>how brief the life of man runs his --ing pilgrimage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 138</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the extravagant and --ing spirit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 154</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a frail vow betwixt an --ing barbarian and a supersubtle Venetian,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.362" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 362</bibl></cit> (cf. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.137" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 1, 137</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>